    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-11-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="465"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Romero</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Mexico</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-11-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 19, 1883</hi>
                        </date>. (Received November 19.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary</hi>: Mr. Mariscal, secretary of foreign
                    relations of the United States of Mexico, advises me last night by cable
                    instructing me to inform the Government of the United States of America that
                    although the Mexican consul at El Paso, Tex., gave timely information <pb
                        facs="0577" n="469" xml:id="pg_469"/> to the authorities of Texas of the
                    assemblage of highwaymen on the territory of the United States of America, 65
                    men, headed by one Lujan, assembled at San Elizario, Tex., and invaded the
                    territory of Mexico, which fact causes the Mexican Government to fear that there
                    exists among those authorities indifference or dissimulation.</p>
                <p>Pray accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">M. Romero.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
